"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"See those red lines? ‚¨áÔ∏è\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/anaLVymuCLdK-91PCpqBe.jpg?height=500&width=1000)\\n\\nYes, they lost it all‚Ä¶\\n\\nBecause they put everything in one basket\\n\\nNow how will YOUR wallet never get hacked?\\n\\nIt‚Äôs easy‚Ä¶\\n\\nby not having one‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶a hacker can‚Äôt tear out your soul\\n\\nbecause you got‚Ä¶\\n\\n*multiple* wallets üßô\\n\\nOops‚Ä¶ there it is now!\\n\\nThat little voice in your head:\\n\\n> ‚ÄúSounds like work‚Ä¶‚Äù\\n\\nOK‚Ä¶\\n\\nif you prefer joining the crew above then go ahead‚Ä¶\\n\\nThe rest of us will be using a browser with profiles:\\n\\nbrave.com\\n\\nNow when a site tries connecting to ‚Äúyour wallet‚Äù‚Ä¶\\n\\n1. you create a new brave profile\\n2. and install a new metamask\\n3. with a new seed phrase\\n\\nSee how easy that is!\\n\\n![If a profile gets compromised, you won‚Äôt be losing your pants](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/OBnvJiXN2xLSPSJ_ZY6UE.jpg?height=482&width=1214)\\n\\nEach profile has *one* purpose and *one* plugin (metamask)\\n\\nOther plugins and casual browsing aren‚Äôt welcome\\n\\n### Bonus tip\\n\\nBookmark your trusted sites because search engines are a devil in disguise üëø\\n\\n[brave.com](https://brave.com) and [metamask.io](https://metamask.io/) is all you need to get started\\n\\nNow go show your friends your new magic trick!\\n\\nThey‚Äôll thank you later üôè\\n\\n\\n---\\n\\n‚Ä¶here comes the FAQ:\\n\\n### Any reason not to do this (a.k.a. I‚Äôm lazy and need an excuse)?\\n\\nOnly if ETH gas fees are giving you nightmares‚Ä¶\\n\\nThen it might not make sense to have a dozen ETH wallets\\n\\nsince you‚Äôd need to keep them all fueled up ‚õΩÔ∏è\\n\\nThough let‚Äôs be honest:\\n\\nif you can afford ETH gas fees‚Ä¶\\n\\nyou can afford cold wallets\\n\\n### Why are search engines a devil in disguise?\\n\\nBecause their ads can easily lure you onto a scam site\\n\\nwhich looks 100% real but robs you of your pants\\n\\nSo only use trusted URLs and bookmark those\\n\\n### Can you help make crypto easier?\\n\\nSimply do as in real life:\\n\\nwhen you walk home from the supermarket‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶do you keep your wallet on your open hand?\\n\\nOf course not‚Ä¶\\n\\nDitto for your crypto wallets‚Ä¶\\n\\nYou close your wallets after each transaction:\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/jZZ-kMziSzBvhmuwKClf5.jpg?height=1440&width=2880)\\n\\n1. hit the colored circle (yours will be different)\\n2. and click the Lock button\\n\\n### But what if I forget?\\n\\nYou can make it automatic:\\n\\n* go in Settings > Advanced\\n* scroll down and fill this in:\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/o4Vk7x8Se_u2u24r0j7aQ.jpg?height=1440&width=2880)\\n\\n### But even when locked, sites stay connected to my wallets\\n\\nYou can disconnect them by going here:\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/4GJfASQRlj5ALn8bVHBdn.jpg?height=1440&width=2880)\\n\\n### How can someone steal my coins?\\n\\nProbably because you approved it ü§Ø\\n\\nWhen first interacting with a contract, you need to give your approval\\n\\nThose approvals are often much higher than they should be‚Ä¶\\n\\nTherefore it‚Äôs best to first click the blue ‚ÄúEdit Permission‚Äù in your metamask popup and lower the approval amount\\n\\n### OK but what about all the stuff I approved in the past?\\n\\nYou can revoke those approvals\\n\\nThere‚Äôs fancy sites popping up left and right to help you do this‚Ä¶\\n\\n‚Ä¶but to be safe I‚Äôll use etherscan.io as example:\\n\\n* go to <https://etherscan.io/tokenapprovalchecker>\\n* look up your wallet address\\n* and to revoke approvals you can connect your wallet using the ‚ÄúConnect to Web3‚Äù button\\n\\nThe process is similar for other chains (teaching you to fish here)\\n\\n### I received some free stuff‚Ä¶ what should I do?\\n\\nAssume it‚Äôs a scam ‚õîÔ∏è\\n\\nNever touch it as it‚Äôll probably drain your wallet\\n\\n### Is this email I received from Metamask safe?\\n\\nMetamask does not have your email so it‚Äôs fake\\n\\n‚Ä¶and so are any other messages you receive\\n\\n### What about seed phrase sharing?\\n\\nI could tell you to ‚Äúnever share your seed phrases‚Äù\\n\\nbut our subconscious mind ignores the ‚Äúnever‚Äù part\\n\\nand you‚Äôd end up making a costly mistake‚Ä¶\\n\\nSo to really help you out here, I‚Äôll need to paint a cruel picture:\\n\\nOnly share a seed phrase when someone points a gun at your child‚Äôs head\\n\\nDon‚Äôt have a child? Then imagine you do\\n\\nOn that dark note, you probably had enough of me now\\n\\nStay safe!\\n\\n\\\\-[sven](https://mirror.xyz/svenow.eth/VBJf8OX7s1LAVKtawCNhSN9bg6K9yKCFv4xIXu2wb_0)\",\"timestamp\":1642427216,\"title\":\"How to NEVER get your hot wallet hacked üî•\"},\"digest\":\"4hWlDwpikWyDRobBrXFqqZSuwIDdrtRaxmWlEr-PcI0\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x89e19d5cF6e9711Acc1E54AC1e87090B2c6C5CAd\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"SFDE7lHaj5iMu5bOEmj87UXPLmyMFFfn-hvL178S_WQ\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"XUS4qViyQ7q6hmZ6-vTubfLpDW9T2hLUVnf-8lhWHRQ\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"IQsaVVgMUqX1UoYHgy0FYcpIRRVPgWCJpUr-ATGX2bWX1LTmJ7-W8PjoNZ5BAkplWThF973lMCOr-m27uXyPSQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x1b38513f9808cd8863a4f59383773b223ab656bf92bb54abb6ff2b9cae0387d87a185c88ec5eab646abab6121904ded90cf5ee847a22a28cdf866ab034d972551c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"SFDE7lHaj5iMu5bOEmj87UXPLmyMFFfn-hvL178S_WQ\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"XUS4qViyQ7q6hmZ6-vTubfLpDW9T2hLUVnf-8lhWHRQ\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"Unaza32DX62RtF35WaGZfVpYTzyIl8A3KKr1F2Ajb0k\"}"